project:
This layout contains all of the object types that are being spawned at runtime.  First and foremost of corse there are the bubbles.  They have all been added to the Bubbles family because they share a common behaviour.  The family has gotten the bullet behaviour, where we make sure that the “bounce of solids” checkmark is set.

The row_id instance variable is there to link a bubble to a marker so that it can fall down every time the timer fires.

the bubble type instance variable just contains the bubble type to compare it.

Finally, the state contains the current state of a bubble;  A bubble can have 3 states: “READY_FOR_LAUNCH”, means that the bubble is in the launcher at is ready to be launched.  Once the user clicks, the state changes too “LAUNCHED”.  And when it arrives at its place, the state becomes “LOCKED”.

There is also a particles effect with a very simple smokey sprite.  The particle effect has rate set to 100, and has a spray cone of 360 degrees.  By making sure that the type is one-shot, it will behave as an explosion.
The particles have a SetColor effect attached to it.  By setting the color at runtime, according to the color of the bubble, we don’t need a particle per bubble color.

Lastly there is also a collision overlay.  It is an object with the same size as a bubble, but is created and destroyed along with a bubble. It exists because handling collisions between 2 objects of the same type in Construct is a bit of a hassle due to the nature the picking and object referencing occurs.
